Though this be not expressed in our Text, yet because it is in order conjoyned with the antecedent words in the Apostles Creed (commonly so called) it will be conveniently in this place joyned to the preceding matter. It is thus gathered from our Text; Peter in the words set down had regard to the Messias, whom all the Prophets had preached, that he would be a King, a Lord, and a most glorious vindicator or restorer of his people And hither also the particle the or that looks in part. For such a Messias the Jews at that time did look for, as appears from Ioh.
