as also in the words of the High-priest, Mat. 26. 63▪ And Christ in his answer following, explaines the matter, how that his dominion is contained in these words.



Use 1. Is of Information, for directing of our faith; 
   •…
o wit, that while we seek remission of our sins, and reconciliation, and salvation in God; we so have our faith in Christ, that we may be specially united to him in his sufferings, blood-shedding, and death, Rom. 3. 25.

Reas. 1. Because Christ's humane nature, of which we here peculiarly speak, came next up in dignity to God himself, by free grace, and personal union and communion with the God-head;
and therefore it was most meet also, that in pr •…
eminence of glory and dignity, he should be next unto God himself.
